This paper deals with quantization of deep neural networks for efficient inference, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the impact of quantization on accuracy, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper explores methods to lower bit-precision beyond quantization limits, which could be relevant to the field of neuromorphic computing (cs.NE) or distributed computing (cs.DC).
